claim.claim-text:
1. A method for managing a credit account having an adjustable credit limit for a customer, the method comprising: 
adjusting the credit limit based on a determination that the credit limit is likely to be reached by a possible transaction made by the customer; 
determining, when the credit limit is adjusted higher, whether the adjusted credit limit is above a maximum credit amount that is based on first predetermined credit amount criteria; 
determining, when the credit limit is adjusted lower, whether the adjusted credit limit is below a minimum credit amount that is based on second predetermined credit amount criteria; and 
revising the adjusted credit limit based on at least one of the determination of whether the adjusted credit limit is above the maximum credit amount and the determination of whether the adjusted credit limit is below the minimum credit amount.

26. A method for managing a credit account having an adjustable credit limit for a customer, the method comprising: 
determining whether the credit limit is likely to be reached by a possible transaction made by the customer when using the account; 
adjusting the credit limit when it is determined that the credit limit is likely to be reached; 
analyzing the adjusted credit limit to determine whether the adjusted credit limit satisfies predefined credit limit amount criteria associated with the account; and 
revising the adjusted credit limit, when the adjusted credit limit does not satisfy the predefined credit amount criteria, such that the revised credit limit satisfies the predetermined credit criteria.

48. A system for managing a credit account having an adjustable credit limit for a customer, the system comprising: 
means for adjusting the credit limit based on a determination that the credit limit is likely to be reached by a possible transaction made by the customer; 
means for determining, when the credit limit is adjusted higher, whether the adjusted credit limit is above a maximum credit amount that is based on first predetermined credit amount criteria; 
means for determining, when the credit limit is adjusted lower, whether the adjusted credit limit is below a minimum credit amount that is based on second predetermined credit amount criteria; and 
means for revising the adjusted credit limit based on at least one of the determination of whether the adjusted credit limit is above the maximum credit amount and the determination of whether the adjusted credit limit is below the minimum credit amount.

73. A system for managing a credit account having an adjustable credit limit for a customer, the system comprising: 
means for determining whether the credit limit is likely to be reached by a possible transaction made by the customer when using the account; 
means for adjusting the credit limit when it is determined that the credit limit is likely to be reached; 
means for analyzing the adjusted credit limit to determine whether the adjusted credit limit satisfies predefined credit limit amount criteria associated with the account; and 
means for revising the adjusted credit limit, when the adjusted credit limit does not satisfy the predefined credit amount criteria, such that the revised credit limit satisfies the predetermined credit criteria.
